SHOPIFY SEO LAUNCH CHECKLIST — Meridian Digital Ltd

A 64-point pre- and post-launch checklist that we run on every Shopify migration, rebuild and new-store launch. The checklist opens with the baseline audit — crawling the current store, snapshotting keyword rankings, traffic, and revenue by landing page, so that any post-launch drops can be diagnosed quickly and precisely. It then walks through URL structure and redirect mapping: the single highest-risk moment of any migration, where a missing 301 can destroy months of compounded rankings.

Subsequent sections cover Shopify theme performance tuning (LCP, CLS and INP budgets for the Dawn theme and popular custom builds), schema markup (Product, Offer, AggregateRating, BreadcrumbList, Organization), image optimisation with srcset and modern formats, internal linking and collection hierarchy, metadata and canonical tags, robots.txt and sitemap configuration, and the exact Google Search Console monitoring cadence for the first 30 days post-launch.

The checklist closes with the ten most common Shopify SEO pitfalls — duplicate collection URLs from filters and tags, thin product pages, canonical loops, missing product schema, and the subtle ways Shopify's default behaviour can silently tank rankings — and the one-page fix for each.
